I went with d5-d6 which allows my b knight to access d7.
White attacks my f knight with his DB to g5.
I now develop my b knight to d7 which is now protecting my f knight.
White takes further control of the centre with pawn to e4.
I attack the centre with d6 to e5.  This is protected by my LB at b7.
As expected white pushes his pawn to e5 which further attacks my knight at f6.
I move pawn a7 to a6.  Not sure why I did not move my f6 knight maybe I should have.

White was keeping the tension and did not take my knight but went with pawn to h3.  I presume this was to prevent my now moving my knight to g4 which would have been the square if I decided to move it.
I decide to move my rook across to e8 I believe I was intending to move my knight to f8.  I also am aware that white's DB could move to h6 and I do not want my rook in the firing line.
White is pushing on the g file now with pawn to g4.
I move my knight to f8 and I expect my opponent is aware I intend to move my knight to g6.
White now takes my f6 knight with his e5 pawn.

I capture with my pawn which may not have been the best move as I had my queen at d8 and if I had taken with my DB and white had captured this then I could have recaptured white's DB with my queen.  I may have not felt I wanted to exchange my DB at this point and I would normally try to keep my DB when I am black.
As I thought white's DB moves to h6 and is now facing my knight at f8.  My king is now on an open file following my capture of white's pawn at f6.
I move my knight to g6 and I was planning to move up to h4 to inhibit white's pawns from any further advance.
Of course white must have seen my thoughts and pushes h3 pawn to h4.
I maintain my knight at g6 as it is protected by the pawns and is a good position for present time.  So I push my e6 pawn to e5 attacking the centre again.
White captures my e5 pawn with his d4 pawn.
I push one of my doubled pawns on the f file to f5 attacking the pawn at g4.
